snippet: The warnings came amid reports of high-pressure sales tactics and efforts to obtain personal information from consumers in advance of the opening of the online markets known as insurance exchanges.
abstract: Obama administrations is warning consumers to beware of possible fraud by con artists taking advantage of new insurance marketplaces being set up under Pres Obama's health care law.
lead_paragraph: The warnings came amid reports of high-pressure sales tactics and efforts to obtain personal information from consumers in advance of the opening of the online markets known as insurance exchanges.
